---
layout: article
title: Functions
description: Run backend code on Appwrite without managing servers. Trigger functions over HTTP, on a schedule, from the SDK, or from events - deploy from Git or a zip, and connect them to Databases, Storage, and Messaging.
back: /docs
---

Appwrite **Functions** runs your server-side code next to your project. Use it when something should not run in the browser or app: webhooks, scheduled jobs, payments, moderation, admin tools, or glue code that talks to other APIs.

Each function has its own URL, [environment variables](/docs/products/functions/environment-variables) for API keys, and a history of [deployments](/docs/products/functions/deployments). When something fails, [executions](/docs/products/functions/executions) and logs help you see what ran.

You can [deploy from Git](/docs/products/functions/deploy-from-git), [develop locally](/docs/products/functions/develop-locally), and pick a [runtime](/docs/products/functions/runtimes) that matches your language. Call functions from HTTP, timers, platform events, or your app with [execute](/docs/products/functions/execute). They work well alongside [Databases](/docs/products/databases), [Storage](/docs/products/storage), and [Messaging](/docs/products/messaging).

