# Build and ship {% #build-and-ship %}

Start from [templates](/docs/products/functions/templates) or your own repo. Use the console to [develop](/docs/products/functions/develop), or work locally, then [deploy from Git](/docs/products/functions/deploy-from-git) or [deploy manually](/docs/products/functions/deploy-manually).

Functions are a good place for checks and side effects you do not want in client code - validation, calling payment or email providers, or updating [Databases](/docs/products/databases) and [Storage](/docs/products/storage) - while [Messaging](/docs/products/messaging) handles outbound mail and push when you use that product.
